id: pm-xsth
title: "CodeFactor/Maintainability: remove useless object-spread fallbacks (unicorn/no-useless-fallback-in-spread ×57)"
description: "**Rule:** `eslint-plugin-unicorn` / `no-useless-fallback-in-spread`. **Count:** 57 (Maintainability, Minor).\n\n**CodeFactor list:** https://www.codefactor.io/repository/github/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/main?category=Maintainability&groupId=10573\n\n## What it is\n\nSpreading `null`/`undefined` into an **object literal** is a no-op, so a `|| {}` / `?? {}` fallback is dead code:\n\n```ts\n{ ...(context ?? {}) }   // ->  { ...context }\n```\n\n## Confirmed instances (grep; verify each is an OBJECT spread)\n\n- `src/cli/main.ts:344`, `src/cli/main.ts:385` — `...(context ?? {})`\n- `src/cli/help-json-payload.ts:334` — `...(runtimeContext ?? {})`\n- `src/cli/help-content.ts:892`\n- `src/cli/commands/test.ts:1227` — `...(linkedTest.env_set ?? {})`\n- ~57 total across `src/**` — see the CodeFactor list for the complete set.\n\n## Important caveat\n\nThe rule applies to **object** spread only. **Array** spread `[...(x ?? [])]` is NOT useless — spreading `undefined` into an array throws — so do NOT strip `?? []` fallbacks. Only remove `?? {}` / `|| {}` inside object literals.\n\n## Fix\n\nLargely auto-fixable (`eslint --fix` once the parity lint exists — see sibling tooling item). Apply, then confirm tests + 100% coverage + typecheck stay green."
type: Chore
status: open
